name: Pepé Skull Flower
description: #41 Skull Flower - Pepé stands 6" high and is arranged in a hand painted vintage brown glass bottle. He has black rhinestone eyes and silver wire pressed into his painted clay head. Old text pages make up the petals and a wooded hand painted dowel is the stem. His jaunty mustache makes him suave addition to any room! Completely handmade by Suzanne Cook and a guaranteed one of a kind.

name: Mohawk Skull Flower
description: #33 Skull Flower - Mohawk stands 5.25" high and is arranged in a tiny glass hand painted bottle. A mohawk of an old rabbit's foot, this funky skull peers at you with his vintage googly eyes pressed into his hand painted clay head. Old text pages make up the petals and a wooded hand painted dowel is the stem. Perfect for your desk! Completely handmade by Suzanne Cook and a guaranteed one of a kind.

name: Melancholy Martha Zombie
description: Doll #14 - Melancholy Martha is a stick zombie puppet with slightly posable arms. She stands 22" high on a striped painted creme and black  1/2" dowel. Her head and hands are made of light air dry clay, hand painted with acrylic. A vintage button eye, wax thread hair and a metal #14 embellish her head. Her arms are batted and wrapped in stained cotton fabric strips. Martha's dress is a combination of strips of chiffon and shiny fabrics in ivory and black. Completely handmade by Suzanne Cook and a guaranteed one of a kind.

name: Vertigo Zombie
description: Doll #22 - Vertigo Zombie is a stick puppet with slightly posable arms. He stands 24" high on a striped painted white and black 1/2" dowel. His head and hands are made of light air dry clay, hand painted with acrylic. A vintage button eye, rhinestone eye, and tattered headband embellish his head. His arms and body are batted and wrapped in stained cheesecloth strips. Vertigo's wears a necklace of metal bells to warn of his arrival. Completely handmade by Suzanne Cook and a guaranteed one of a kind.
